 , range or ammo slot)<br><br>GEHIT<br>Wizard  Tallon Zek<br><br>  VENI<br>  VIDI<br>  MORTI<br><br><a href="http://www.gaijindesign.com/lawriemalen/jedi" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.gaijindesign.com/lawriemalen/jedi/sithlord.jpg" width="285" height="123" border="0">:: how jedi are you? ::</a><br> <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugehit.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gehit</A> at: 8/13/02 12:23:48 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/usinladarie.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sinladarie</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/14/02 9:38:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=88.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Clarify differences between PvP servers plz, and help me</span><hr size=1> There are actually a fair number of differences between the different PvP servers.<br><br>Sullon Zek (my home) is a no holds barred, no rules (except no swearing) server...NOT a place for the faint of heart.  Once you ding 6 you are fair game to any member of the opposing team, so you can fully expect to die ALOT at the hands of high level players.  It's a fact of life...get used to it (if your toon dying stresses you out then don't go with a PvP server).  It's a low population server and there is an incredible imbalance in the teams at the moment.  Evil is far larger than the other two, but really, given the low population, plenty of opportunities exist for everyone.<br><br>You can kill members of your own team simply by /duel.<br><br>Killing a cleric...I can't speak for the higher levels, but at the low and mid range it really is a waste of your time to even try to solo against a cleric.  You've already seen what happens...they will oom you out trying to kill them, heal everything you've done and then cast/melee you to death, and trust me they are not going to sit there waiting for you to oom, they have plenty of weapons at their disposal. <br><br>I'm a relative lowbie (mid 30's) and someone like Velael who is high level and has been playing the game for quite awhile would be better able to discuss the high end PvP (and probably knows alot of tactics for dealing with clerics that I haven't figured out yet).  I just don't do clerics in a solo situation if I can avoid it...its a waste of my time and dying or gating isn't how I want a PvP encounter to end...now in group pvp that's different, and much more fun...<br><br>Oh and you will need to adjust your thinking on gear.  On a red server resist gear is far more important (blue diamonds are your friends <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   ) and you can expect any player with a brain to be sporting decent resists especially for FR CR and MR which can really cut back on your damage dealing capacity.  Alot of players will actually will have two sets of gear, a PvE set and a PvP set which will be heavily resist oriented.<br><br>Moving from a blue server to a red one is a big change, but after playing on SZ, I wouldn't even consider playing on a blue server.  <br><br>Have fun wherever you go.<br><br>Sin <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uferacitus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Feracitus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/16/02 8:29:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=88.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://discovirtual.uol.com.br/feracitus/Compartilhada/feravatar.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top